## 4. Character Frequency Count

### Basic Frequency Count
```java
// Time: O(n) | Space: O(1)
public static int[] charFrequency(String s) {
    int[] freq = new int[26]; // lowercase only
    for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
        freq[c - 'a']++;
    }
    return freq;
}

// Print frequency
public static void printFrequency(String s) {
    int[] freq = new int[256]; // all ASCII
    for (char c : s.toCharArray()) freq[c]++;
    for (int i = 0; i < 256; i++) {
        if (freq[i] > 0) {
            System.out.println((char) i + " : " + freq[i]);
        }
    }
}
```

### Most Frequent Character
```java
public static char mostFrequent(String s) {
    int[] freq = new int[256];
    for (char c : s.toCharArray()) freq[c]++;
    int max = 0;
    char result = s.charAt(0);
    for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
        if (freq[c] > max) {
            max = freq[c];
            result = c;
        }
    }
    return result;
}
```

### Top K Frequent Characters
```java
// Time: O(n) | Space: O(n) — Bucket Sort approach
public static List<Character> topKFrequent(String s, int k) {
    int[] freq = new int[26];
    for (char c : s.toCharArray()) freq[c - 'a']++;

    // Bucket: index = frequency, value = list of chars
    List<Character>[] bucket = new List[s.length() + 1];
    for (int i = 0; i < 26; i++) {
        if (freq[i] > 0) {
            if (bucket[freq[i]] == null) bucket[freq[i]] = new ArrayList<>();
            bucket[freq[i]].add((char)('a' + i));
        }
    }

    List<Character> result = new ArrayList<>();
    for (int i = bucket.length - 1; i >= 0 && result.size() < k; i--) {
        if (bucket[i] != null) result.addAll(bucket[i]);
    }
    return result.subList(0, Math.min(k, result.size()));
}
```

