## 5. Bucket Algorithm Problems

The **Bucket Algorithm** uses an array where the **index represents the value/frequency**, allowing O(n) sorting/grouping.

### Problem 1: Sort Characters By Frequency
```java
// "tree" → "eert" (e appears 2x)
// Time: O(n) | Space: O(n)
public static String frequencySort(String s) {
    int[] freq = new int[256];
    for (char c : s.toCharArray()) freq[c]++;

    // Bucket: index = frequency
    List<Character>[] bucket = new List[s.length() + 1];
    for (int i = 0; i < 256; i++) {
        if (freq[i] > 0) {
            int f = freq[i];
            if (bucket[f] == null) bucket[f] = new ArrayList<>();
            bucket[f].add((char) i);
        }
    }

    StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
    for (int i = bucket.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        if (bucket[i] != null) {
            for (char c : bucket[i]) {
                for (int j = 0; j < i; j++) sb.append(c);
            }
        }
    }
    return sb.toString();
}
```

### Problem 2: Minimum Number of Steps to Make Anagram
```java
// Count characters that differ
// Time: O(n) | Space: O(1)
public static int minSteps(String s, String t) {
    int[] freq = new int[26];
    for (char c : s.toCharArray()) freq[c - 'a']++;
    for (char c : t.toCharArray()) freq[c - 'a']--;

    int steps = 0;
    for (int f : freq) if (f > 0) steps += f;
    return steps;
}
```

### Problem 3: Find All Anagrams in String (Sliding Window + Bucket)
```java
// Find start indices of all anagrams of p in s
// Time: O(n) | Space: O(1)
public static List<Integer> findAnagrams(String s, String p) {
    List<Integer> result = new ArrayList<>();
    if (s.length() < p.length()) return result;

    int[] pFreq = new int[26];
    int[] window = new int[26];

    for (char c : p.toCharArray()) pFreq[c - 'a']++;

    int k = p.length();
    for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
        window[s.charAt(i) - 'a']++;

        if (i >= k) window[s.charAt(i - k) - 'a']--;

        if (Arrays.equals(window, pFreq)) result.add(i - k + 1);
    }
    return result;
}
```

### Problem 4: Ransom Note (Bucket)
```java
// Can ransom note be made from magazine letters?
// Time: O(n) | Space: O(1)
public static boolean canConstruct(String ransomNote, String magazine) {
    int[] freq = new int[26];
    for (char c : magazine.toCharArray()) freq[c - 'a']++;
    for (char c : ransomNote.toCharArray()) {
        if (--freq[c - 'a'] < 0) return false;
    }
    return true;
}
```

